Male.description: Golden-cheeked Warblers have a thin black eyeline and a black crown while Black-throated Green Warblers have a dark ear patch and a yellow-olive crown.

Female.description: Female Golden-cheeked Warblers have a thin black eyeline and a gray back while female Black-throated Green Warblers have a dark ear patch and a yellow-olive back.

Adult male.description: Hermit Warblers have a clean yellow face and an unstreaked breast unlike Black-throated Green Warblers. Breeding ranges do not overlap.

Female/immature.description: Hermit Warblers have a clean yellow face and an unstreaked breast unlike Black-throated Green Warblers. Breeding ranges do not overlap.

Adult male.description: Townsend's Warblers have a black (not yellow-olive) crown and a yellow (not white) breast. No range overlap.

Immature.description: Immature Townsend's Warblers have a yellow (not white) breast and a bolder cheek patch than immature Black-throated Green Warblers. No range overlap.
